Governor Abdullahi Sule, of Nasarawa State, has approved the appointment of Barr Muhammad Ubandoma Aliyu, as the new Secretary to the State Government (SSG). Barrister Aliyu, is the younger brother of Inspector General of Police, IGP Mohammed Adamu. A statement signed by the spokesperson of the governor, Yakubu Lamai, said the appointment took effect from yesterday. It would be recalled that the former SSG, Ahmed Tijjani Aliyu, was sacked on Monday, following his indictment for alleged fraud by the Nasarawa State House of Assembly. The state legislators asked Ahmed-Tijani who was immediate past commissioner of education, to refund over N248.5 million as unaccounted funds to the state government. The fund was part of monies earmarked for renovation of schools. The Lawyer accused the former SSG of displaying blatant inefficiency, incompetence and ineffectiveness in the performance of his official duties and urged the governor to relief him of his appointment. Our correspondent reports that the new SSG, Muhammad Ubandoma Aliyu, obtained his first degree in 1987 from University of Maiduguri and holds a Law degree from University of Jos. “His Excellency Engr Abdullahi A. Sule, the Executive Governor of Nasarawa State, has affirmed his confidence in the proven capacity illustrated track record and tested integrity of Barrister Muhammad Ubandoma Aliyu, to serve with competence, unalloyed loyalty and unbridled sense of purpose in the office off Secretary to the Government of Nasarawa State” the statement said.